Subject:
USIEF Mentoring Workshop

Body:
b'     Dear Students,    USIEF in association with IndoGerman Center for Sustainability (IGCS) is organizing a halfday mentoring workshop at IIT Madras on Monday, June 20, 2016, 9.30 a.m. to 2 p.m. (Venue: I.C.&S.R. Halls I & II)     This workshop is meant for potential candidates preparing to apply for the FulbrightKalam Climate Fellowship  and will have presentations by USIEF staff and Fulbright alumni on the application process and elements of a strong application (writing a good research proposal or personal statement and getting effective letters of recommendation). They will also conduct a Digital Video Conference with a FulbrightNehru Postdoctoral Research scholar Dr. Saleem Khan Amsad Ibrahim Khan. Dr. Saleem is based at Columbia University, New York.    We are inviting Ph.D. and PostDoctoral scholars  working on research topics related to climate.  Number of registrations is limited to a maximum of 45, and this will be done on first come first serve basis.    All students who are interested in participating may kindly inform Prof. B. S. Murty of Civil Engineering by email ( bsm@iitm.ac.in ) latest by 5:00 PM on Friday 17June2016.      All the faculty members are requested to kindly bring this to the notice of the scholars working under them.    Thank you and with warm regards    Yours sincerely  B.S. Murty  bsm@iitm.ac.in ; Phone: 04422574262; Mobile: 9840079    '

